I love how people are leaving comments and stupid(huge) invites as if they are talking to the photographer like they would with any other photographer here on flickr, not realizing that this image is from 1942 and a part of the Library of Congress. lol. 

@Blank- This isn't a colored photograph, this is a color photograph.
@Erikkellison- This photo is quite possible to produce without editing, today and in 1942 alike, although I think it's a bit easier to achieve today. As Didge explained, the image is under exposed for the background, and then an off-camera flash (positioned at camera left presumably) most likely fitted with an umbrealla or other diffuser is used to illuminate the subject. The use of a diffuser and properly dialed-in flash is why the lighting is not harsh.

